		Could you provide us a MCVE (See <denchmark-link:https://stackoverflow.com/help/mcve>https://stackoverflow.com/help/mcve</denchmark-link>
) that involves only a single TensorFlow operation and the results have large difference with data format NHWC and NCHW with a particular input?
Also, could you give it a try after setting 'TF_CUDNN_USE_AUTOTUNE' to '0' with NHWC data format to see if that helps? Winograd convolution that is used in case of NHWC is known to have higher numerical error. See section 4 in <denchmark-link:https://openreview.net/pdf?id=H1ZaRZVKg>https://openreview.net/pdf?id=H1ZaRZVKg</denchmark-link>
